```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+s+=+%22%22;%0A++++assert!(s.is_empty());%0A++++%0A++++let+s+=+%22not+empty%22;%0A++++assert!(!s.is_empty());%0A%7D&edition=2021)

1.9.0 Â· [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/str/mod.rs.html#209)

Checks that `index`\-th byte is the first byte in a UTF-8 code point sequence or the end of the string.

The start and end of the string (when `index == self.len()`) are considered to be boundaries.

Returns `false` if `index` is greater than `self.len()`.

